      "question": "A solid metallic cylinder of base radius $6$ $\\text{cm}$ and height $10$ $\\text{cm}$ is melted and recast into $15$ identical small solid cones, each of radius $2$ $\\text{cm}$. If the height of each small cone is $h$, then the value of $h$ is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Step 1: Calculate the volume of the original cylinder using $V = \\pi r^2 h$.",
          "Step 2: Express the volume of one cone as $V_{cone} = \\frac{1}{3} \\pi r^2 h$.",
          "Step 3: Equate the volume of the cylinder to the sum of the volumes of $15$ cones: $V_{cyl} = 15 \\times V_{cone}$.",
          "Step 4: Solve the resulting equation for $h$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$V_{cyl} = \\pi \\times (6)^2 \\times 10 = 360\\pi \\text{ cm}^3 \\\\ 15 \\times V_{cone} = 15 \\times (\\frac{1}{3} \\times \\pi \\times (2)^2 \\times h) \\\\ 360\\pi = 15 \\times \\frac{4}{3} \\pi h \\\\ 360 = 20h \\\\ h = \\frac{360}{20} = 18 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
      "topic": "Surface Areas and Volumes",
      "subtopic": "Conversion of solids",
      "marks": 1,
